-The death penalty.

00:07.240 --> 00:10.232
Really? That's a--
That's a very complex issue.

00:10.400 --> 00:12.118
So-- So, what are your thoughts?

00:12.280 --> 00:14.999
lf you're going to the chair
they give you what you want. . .

00:15.160 --> 00:16.479
. . .for your last meal.

00:16.640 --> 00:17.959
l guess.

00:18.120 --> 00:21.874
-l'm gonna order cereal.
-Why?

00:22.040 --> 00:25.874
Because if you keep adding milk
you can make it last forever.

00:26.520 --> 00:29.239
And they just gotta wait.

00:29.960 --> 00:31.791
Okay, let's go back a bit.

00:31.960 --> 00:34.838
Why would you be going to the chair
in the first place?

00:35.000 --> 00:38.436
l don't know.
My DNA shows up at a murder scene. . .

00:38.760 --> 00:42.673
. . .because it's planted by a crooked cop
or maybe one of my teachers.

00:43.240 --> 00:46.835
-So you'd be wrongly accused?
-Story of my life, Dad.

00:48.000 --> 00:50.514
Remember that water pistol incident
at school?

00:50.680 --> 00:52.352
But that was your water pistol.

00:52.520 --> 00:55.273
Yes, but it wasn't my pee.

00:57.440 --> 00:58.873
Morning.

00:59.040 --> 01:00.268
Oh, hey, how was your run?

01:00.440 --> 01:02.908
Great. We made it
all the way to the pier and back.

01:03.080 --> 01:04.876
Didn't we, honey?

01:06.360 --> 01:07.952
Yeah.

01:08.320 --> 01:10.470
Pier. Back.

01:11.600 --> 01:13.795
Hey, Jake,
you ever seen anybody cough up blood?

01:14.760 --> 01:16.671
-Nope.
-Then pay attention.

01:17.360 --> 01:20.591
-Ass.
-Ass?

01:20.800 --> 01:22.438
Kiss.

01:23.120 --> 01:24.712
My.

01:25.480 --> 01:27.311
Sweaty.

01:29.560 --> 01:32.836
l think l'll jump in the shower.
Wanna join me?

01:33.000 --> 01:34.592
Can't.

01:35.120 --> 01:36.633
Later.

01:36.800 --> 01:38.472
Maybe.

01:39.120 --> 01:41.839
All right. Well,
you drink your health shake, all right?

01:42.000 --> 01:44.514
-You'll feel better.
-Doubt it.

01:48.760 --> 01:51.718
-What's in that?
-l don't know.

01:51.880 --> 01:54.110
Vitamins, minerals, protein.

01:54.280 --> 01:57.556
Whatever it is, it's flushing out stuff
l ate in high school.

02:00.120 --> 02:03.874
Hey, do you think they let you
have a last poop after your last meal?

02:07.560 --> 02:08.595
What?

02:08.759 --> 02:10.955
Because as long as you're sitting on
the can. . .

02:11.120 --> 02:13.429
. . .technically you're still pooping.

02:14.400 --> 02:15.753
And they gotta wait.

02:16.840 --> 02:17.875
Go get dressed.

02:18.400 --> 02:21.597
lf they made you hold one in,
that'd be cruel and unusual punishment.

02:26.200 --> 02:28.589
You know, l am impressed
with what you're doing here.

02:28.760 --> 02:32.275
Exercising, eating right,
laying off the cigars and the booze.

02:32.440 --> 02:34.510
l mean,
Mia has really done wonders with you.

02:34.680 --> 02:36.591
-Yeah, she's an incredible woman.
-She is.

02:36.760 --> 02:38.352
-And l'm a lucky guy.
-You are.

02:38.520 --> 02:40.511
Why is there
this little voice in my head. . .

02:40.680 --> 02:43.717
. . .that keeps whispering,
''Kill yourself. Do it now. ''

02:45.000 --> 02:46.672
Don't worry about that. lt's common.

02:46.840 --> 02:47.829
-Really?
-Oh, yeah.

02:48.000 --> 02:51.549
Every man who gets into a long-term,
committed relationship hears that voice.

02:51.720 --> 02:54.075
Mine sounded a little like Alec Baldwin.

02:54.240 --> 02:55.275
l don't know why.

02:55.440 --> 02:57.874
Maybe because l enjoyed him
in that submarine movie.

02:58.360 --> 03:00.669
-What was that call--?
-Would you get to the point?

03:00.840 --> 03:03.479
You have to remember that over time
that voice will fade. . .

03:03.640 --> 03:05.517
. . .when you realize
what you're giving up. . .

03:05.680 --> 03:07.636
. . .is nothing compared
to what you're gaining.

03:07.800 --> 03:09.518
What exactly am l gaining?

03:09.680 --> 03:11.671
Are you kidding?
You're gaining a soul mate.

03:11.840 --> 03:13.956
Someone to walk down life's path
with you.

03:14.120 --> 03:16.509
Someone who'll always be there,
sharing your hopes. . .

03:16.680 --> 03:18.716
. . .your joys and your sorrows.

03:19.040 --> 03:20.359
You got nothing.

03:22.240 --> 03:24.708
That's what the minister said
at my wedding.

03:27.280 --> 03:29.316
Hunt for Red October.

03:37.480 --> 03:40.199
Be back in a while, honey.
l'm going for a power walk.

03:40.360 --> 03:43.796
-Pace yourself.
-Don't worry.

