if you don't give me 20 bucks. . .

05:19.960 --> 05:21.712
. . .l'm gonna tell on you.

05:23.120 --> 05:24.792
That's blackmail.

05:25.800 --> 05:27.233
Well, then, yeah.

05:33.200 --> 05:36.397
-Oh, hi, Mom, how are you?
-Deeply hurt.

05:37.120 --> 05:38.439
ls this about me or Charlie?

05:38.600 --> 05:40.352
-Charlie.
-Great. Come on in.

05:43.880 --> 05:47.714
Can you explain to me how your brother
can be in a serious relationship. . .

05:47.880 --> 05:49.836
. . .and not only
have l not met the woman. . .

05:50.000 --> 05:52.560
. . .he hasn't even bothered
to tell me her name?

05:52.720 --> 05:54.676
Do you really need an explanation
for that?

05:54.840 --> 05:56.432
Do you want it to be about you?

05:56.960 --> 05:59.952
-Her name's Mia. She's in the kitchen.
-Thank you.

06:02.200 --> 06:04.111
Thank God l didn't know Anne Frank.

06:07.280 --> 06:08.429
Hello.

06:10.520 --> 06:12.033
Hello.

06:16.160 --> 06:19.869
-l'm Evelyn, Charlie's mother.
-l'm Mia, Charlie's girlfriend.

06:20.480 --> 06:23.358
-So we finally meet.
-So we do.

06:24.760 --> 06:25.829
One question.

06:26.600 --> 06:29.478
-l'm listening.
-Can you fix him?

06:30.200 --> 06:31.315
l'm trying.

06:33.000 --> 06:37.471
Fifteen, 1 6, 1 7, 1 8--

06:37.640 --> 06:39.198
Jake?

06:39.440 --> 06:41.237
How about a hug
for your grandmommy?

06:41.560 --> 06:43.357
No, thank you.

06:44.480 --> 06:46.072
One, two--

06:54.640 --> 06:56.596
What the hell are you doing?

06:56.760 --> 06:58.910
Hey, hey, hey. Keep it down.
Keep it down.

06:59.080 --> 07:00.957
Mia thinks l'm taking a power walk.

07:02.720 --> 07:05.553
This is a sad, sad day.

07:07.280 --> 07:09.748
l always figured
you'd be the last guy in the world. . .

07:09.920 --> 07:11.990
. . .to end up whipped.

07:12.400 --> 07:15.312
l am not whipped. l'm considerate.

07:16.120 --> 07:17.712
-Considerate?
-Yeah.

07:17.880 --> 07:19.757
See, l love Mia
and want her to be happy.

07:19.920 --> 07:22.480
l happen to know she's not happy
when l smoke cigars. . .

07:22.640 --> 07:25.074
. . .and drink and gamble
and stay out all night. . .

07:25.240 --> 07:29.597
. . .and eat meat and sugar and grease
and fat and nap and swear. . .

07:29.760 --> 07:31.751
. . .and wear shorts
and bowling shirts. . . .

07:31.920 --> 07:35.276
Charlie, you ain't just whipped,
you're roped, saddled and gelded.

07:35.440 --> 07:39.069
They could use you
to give rides at kid's birthday parties.

07:39.240 --> 07:42.038
-l am not whipped.
-Yeah.

07:42.640 --> 07:46.189
Here, might as well take one
of these sacks since yours is empty.

07:46.360 --> 07:48.794
Hang on a second.

07:48.960 --> 07:52.157
-That ain't gonna do it, Alice.
-What?

07:52.320 --> 07:55.471
You smell like a beer bottle
that just fell out of Joe Camel's ass.

07:56.600 --> 07:58.113
Well, what am l supposed to do?

07:58.280 --> 08:00.714
Oh, hang on,
let's see if l got anything in here. . .

08:00.880 --> 08:03.519
. . .that might mask your stench.

08:03.680 --> 08:05.398
Oven cleaner. No.

08:06.040 --> 08:08.315
Ty-D-Bol. No.

08:08.480 --> 08:11.756
How do you feel about taking a whore's
bath with a hunk of blue cheese?

08:13.400 --> 08:16.392
l'm so proud of him. He hasn't had
a drop of alcohol in weeks.

08:16.560 --> 08:18.391
Well, that's one way to go.

08:18.560 --> 08:22.758
But l've found that men who drink
tend to talk less and sleep more.

08:23.480 --> 08:25.789
Which, frankly,
becomes increasingly desirable. . .

08:25.960 --> 08:27.678
. . .as the years go by.

08:31.320 --> 08:33.356
Oh, this can't be good.

08:34.120 --> 08:36.429
Hello, darling. Wonderful to see you.

08:36.600 --> 08:38.078
Hi, Mom.

08:39.640 --> 08:40.833
Have you been dusting?

08:42.360 --> 08:45.591
