09:38.360 --> 09:40.078
l forgot who l'm dealing with.

09:40.240 --> 09:42.231
l know you have to hide
to smoke a cigar. . .

09:42.400 --> 09:44.038
. . .and slam back a warm beer.

09:44.320 --> 09:45.719
What'd you do, bug my garage?

09:45.880 --> 09:47.029
Don't be paranoid.

09:47.200 --> 09:49.270
l have a long-standing arrangement
with Jake.

09:50.200 --> 09:52.475
Charlie, l'm ready.

09:55.960 --> 09:57.075
l'm out here.

09:57.240 --> 09:59.196
Go, go, go.

09:59.360 --> 10:02.079
Okay, l'll go,
but l want you to remember one thing.

10:02.240 --> 10:04.356
-What?
-l'm not gonna wait for you forever.

10:10.880 --> 10:12.598
How do l look?

10:24.200 --> 10:25.189
How's your couscous?

10:26.480 --> 10:27.959
Yum, yum.

10:28.800 --> 10:30.870
l had an interesting chat
with your mom today.

10:31.040 --> 10:33.110
Yeah, l'm sorry about that.

10:33.280 --> 10:36.989
l know she comes on a little strong
but her heart's in the right place.

10:37.160 --> 10:41.358
lf you mean in a cooler on its way to a
dying man in Tennessee, then we agree.

10:41.960 --> 10:45.191
-You can't possibly mean that.
-l suppose not.

10:45.360 --> 10:48.079
She's too selfish to donate an organ.

10:48.400 --> 10:49.674
Even one she doesn't use.

10:50.280 --> 10:52.555
That's so unfair, Charlie.
Your mother loves you.

10:53.040 --> 10:56.191
Really? Did she or did she not say
l was a bitter disappointment?

10:56.920 --> 10:58.956
