-Yeah, l guess.

17:01.920 --> 17:04.275
Look, see,
there's stairs right over there. Just--

17:04.440 --> 17:06.112
Anyway. . .

17:06.280 --> 17:07.998
. . .l was thinking that you and Mia. . .

17:08.160 --> 17:11.357
. . .would like to join us for dinner
one night. You know, double date.

17:12.119 --> 17:14.634
Oh, well, that's nice, Rose,
but l broke up with Mia.

17:15.560 --> 17:18.438
Oh, l see.

17:18.720 --> 17:20.358
Well, then goodbye, Gordon.

17:34.320 --> 17:36.788
l think l made a big mistake.

17:36.960 --> 17:38.632
l know the feeling.

17:38.800 --> 17:42.713
l once ate an egg salad sandwich
l left in my desk over the weekend.

17:44.200 --> 17:46.111
Huge mistake.

17:46.760 --> 17:48.159
My relationship with Mia. . .

17:48.320 --> 17:51.232
. . .was the best thing that happened
to me and l threw it away.

17:51.600 --> 17:54.160
That's what l should have done
with the sandwich.

17:55.200 --> 17:57.395
l wonder if it's too late to fix things.

17:57.560 --> 17:59.278
Call her and find out.

17:59.440 --> 18:01.715
But if l do,
l'll be right back where l started. . .

18:01.880 --> 18:04.110
. . .trying to be somebody l'm not.

18:04.280 --> 18:06.077
Okay, then find another girlfriend.

18:06.240 --> 18:09.312
l don't want another girlfriend.
l want Mia.

18:09.480 --> 18:11.357
Then call her.

18:11.680 --> 18:13.398
l can't.

18:13.560 --> 18:16.233
l can't live with her,
l can't live without her.

18:16.400 --> 18:20.871
lf your plane crashed in the Andes
and she died, could you eat her?

18:33.160 --> 18:35.276
Mia, it's Charlie.

18:35.440 --> 18:39.638
Look, you win. l'll change.
No more meat, l promise.

18:42.040 --> 18:44.508
Come on, Mia.
Come out and smell me.

18:46.240 --> 18:49.471
Mia's not here.
Do l have to smell you?

18:50.040 --> 18:51.792
-Who are you?
-Ginger.

18:51.960 --> 18:53.279
So you're Charlie.

18:53.440 --> 18:57.069
-Yeah, where's Mia?
-Hang on a minute.

18:57.720 --> 19:00.632
She told me to give you this
if you stopped by.

19:03.440 --> 19:05.510
She took a job in New York?
Why'd she do that?

19:05.680 --> 19:06.999
Just read the note.

19:07.640 --> 19:10.791
''l love you too much to try to make you
into something you're not. . .

19:10.960 --> 19:14.475
. . .and l love me too much
to settle for who you are. ''

19:14.640 --> 19:17.029
That's the part
that always makes me cry.

19:18.880 --> 19:21.269
l can change her mind.
l'll fly to New York tonight.

19:21.440 --> 19:23.271
-Do you have her address?
-Come on in.

19:24.440 --> 19:26.795
-Can l get you something to drink?
-No, thanks.

19:27.200 --> 19:29.191
Hi, American Airlines,
reservations please.

19:29.360 --> 19:31.590
You sure? l got all my boys here.

19:31.760 --> 19:33.557
Jack, Johnnie and Jose.

19:33.720 --> 19:37.030
Maybe a poquito Jose.

19:38.600 --> 19:40.079
Are these actual baby back ribs?

19:40.240 --> 19:42.800
-Yeah, help yourself.
-Thanks.

19:44.280 --> 19:47.352
l'd like to make a reservation
on the redeye to New York tonight.

19:47.520 --> 19:50.830
Hey, do you mind if l turn on the TV?
l've got some money on the Lakers.

19:51.000 --> 19:53.070
-You bet sports?
-l'll bet anything.

19:53.240 --> 19:55.708
l had 200 bucks
on my sister's pregnancy test.

19:57.320 --> 19:58.753
How exactly do you know Mia?

19:58.920 --> 20:02.799
Oh, we used to do the ballet thing
together but l didn't have the discipline.

20:03.240 --> 20:06.949
-No kidding.
-l still dance, but just for tips.

20:08.960 --> 20:10.029
l'll call you back.

20:14.640 --> 20:17.074
You know, l'm thinking
she probably needs her space.

20:17.240 --> 20:18.389
Probably.

20:18.760 --> 20:21.638
-Mind if l hang out and watch the game?
-Be my guest.

20:27.320 --> 20:30.471
lf you got cash,
l could give you a lap dance at halftime.

20:33.560 --> 20:35.471
That'd be swell.

